 SPACING
 When text is entered in a document, the space between lines depends
mostly on the size of the font being used. Larger fonts will have larger

areas between lines to allow room for letters that descend below the main
line, such as "y", "j", "p", and "q".

 Final Copy enables you to choose from four spacing -- single, 1-1/2,
double, and variable. The chart below shows you important information for
each type of spacing.

    SPACING      HEIGHT OF LINE	       MAXIMUM LINE HEIGHT

    Single       120% of line's largest font  240 pts
    1-1/2	180% of line's largest font   18 pts
    Double       240% of line's largest font   24 pts
    Variable     Spacing is based on tallest leading value of line

