			     TEXT AND FONTS
 High quality output is probably one of the main reasons you chose Final
Copy as your word processor. Final Copy lets you define your text's font,
size, style, position, width, case, colour, and oblique percentage. All
the commands you will need work effectively with text can be found in the
"Text" menu. The settings may be made all at once using the "Type Specs"
command (explained later in this chapter), or one at a time using other
commands in the "Text" menu.

			      OPENING FONTS
 SoftSans is the Final Copy default font. Before you may use another font
in your document, you must first open it.

 TO OPEN A FINAL COPY FONT:
------------------------------------------------------------------------
